</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102294-0022 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 090933 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 22, 1994, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 3; Column 2; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
64 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DONAHUE'S TOUCH REACHES SOUTH BEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Don't worry about Lou Holtz keeping his winning percentage up. This year's 
schedule includes Northwestern, Purdue, Navy and Air Force.Next season, he adds 
powerful Army and Vanderbilt. 
</P>
<P>
 At the pace the program is demising, I wouldn't be surprised to see him 
schedule Texas El Paso and New Mexico State. 
</P>
<P>
 Terry Donahue would be proud of Lou's foresight. 
</P>
<P>
 FRANK CALIRI 
