TROJAN FAN ASKS: WHO'S STUPID NOW? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I wonder if Stanford Coach Bill Walsh has learned his lesson? 
</P>
<P>
 Recently, he has insulted USC players, coaches and faculty with remarks that 
he hopes would lead you to believe that they have low mentalities and are just 
plain stupid. He referred to USC as "Yesterday U." 
</P>
<P>
 Well, when "Yesterday U" played Stanford last Saturday, it won. And the best 
part was that it was helped by two penalties against Stanford for having 12 men 
on the field. 
</P>
<P>
 Twice? Now that's stupid! 
</P>
