Disney's Hollywood Pictures won a $3-million fight for the film rights to the 
book, acting on behalf of actor and filmmaker Robert Redford.The book is a 
first-time effort by British filmmaker Nicholas Evans. Rachel Pfeffer at 
Redford's Wildwood Productions was said to be instrumental in obtaining the 
project. The deal was arranged by agents Bob Bookman, Matthew Snyder and Eileen 
Rapke at Creative Artists Agency, as well as London-based Nick Marston and 
Caradoc King at A.P. Watt Ltd. 
