<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASE THE JOINT FOR SUITABLE USES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here are some decorative possibilities for suitcases: 
</P>
<P>
 * Stack three or four as a bedside or sofa table, or place them at the foot of 
the bed to store linens and blankets. 
</P>
<P>
 * Top a stack of sturdy cases with a piece of glass or plastic laminate for 
use as a small dining table or occasional table. 
</P>
<P>
 * Stack several cases atop a tall chest for storage of out-of-season clothes. 
</P>
<P>
 * Put a train case on a dressing table to hold makeup. 
</P>
<P>
 * Use wicker cases or picnic baskets in the kitchen to store utensils or 
foodstuffs that don't need refrigeration. 
</P>
<P>
 * Put a children's camp trunk near the back door to store boots or sports 
equipment. 
