<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRL KILLED AFTER A WARNING NOT TO TALK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who warned a group of friends that he would shoot the next person who 
talked shot a 14-year-old girl to death when she spoke, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Nina Scott was shot in the forehead as she and her friends sat on her 
grandmother's porch.Kevin Barnes, 18, of Lonoke was charged with first-degree 
murder Wednesday and is being held on $100,000 bond. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was totally senseless. It was horseplay," said Police Chief Floyd Van 
Horne. "There was no physical altercation, no verbal argument. You had six 
young people sitting on a porch talking." 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Coleman, Nina's aunt, said the other friends told her that Barnes pulled 
the gun on two of them and then issued his warning. 
</P>
<P>
 "He said: 'I'm going to shoot whoever says the next word.' That was Nina," 
Coleman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's grandmother, Lillie Belle Dodson, said she was inside the house 
when the shooting occurred Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "I jumped up and went to see what had happened. Nina had been shot. She was 
lying over there and the porch was full of blood." Dodson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
