<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIANA VISITS AMERICAN RED CROSS HEADQUARTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Princess Diana paid a private visit to American Red Cross headquarters Friday, 
extending a scheduled half an hour meeting with the group's president, 
Elizabeth Hanford Dole. 
</P>
<P>
 The two discussed ways the American and British Red Cross can work together to 
drum up more aid for victims of disasters and conflicts around the world. 
</P>
<P>
 Diana arrived in Washington late Thursday after spending a day in New York 
City. In Washington, she is staying with a friend, Lucia Flecha de Lima, wife 
of Brazilian Ambassador Paolo Tarso Flecha de Lima. 
</P>
</TEXT>
