<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; CITY 
COUNCIL OKS 2% RAISE FOR DEPARTMENT MANAGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council approved a 2% salary increase for department 
general managers, matching the raises most other city workers got earlier this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 But agency chiefs will not automatically receive the 2% raise that other 
workers get next year. Mayor Richard Riordan and the council are considering 
modifications in the merit pay plan for general managers. The council also 
approved a 9% raise over three years for some managers and non-union employees 
of the Department of Water and Power. Union workers won a 9% raise after 
striking last fall. 
</P>
<P>
 The salary package approved today covers 1,100 full-time and 7,100 part- time 
employees but excludes DWP managers who earn more than $70,000 a year. 
</P>
