<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRESPI EDGES ST. PAUL IN FINAL SECONDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE GALLUZZO, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dave Lins' nine-yard touchdown pass to Marcos Solorzano with 12 seconds 
remaining Friday night lifted Crespi High to a dramatic 14-13 upset over 
previously undefeated St. Paul in a Del Rey League game. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'd run that play three or four times earlier in the game, but always to the 
flop side," Crespi Coach Tim Lins said of the decisive play."This time Dave 
went to the other side where there was man-to-man coverage."  
</P>
<P>
 The key play of the 14-play, 49-yard drive came on fourth and one at the St. 
Paul 22-yard line when Lins caught his batted pass and ran around right end for 
a first down. "It was supposed to be a hitch and go," said Lins, who completed 
21 of 24 attempts for 164 yards. "We got lucky. The ball came right back to me 
and I just ran." 
</P>
<P>
 Crespi (4-3 overall, 2-0 in league play) capped an eight-play, 55-yard drive 
with a 17-yard option pass from wide receiver Wayne Emerson to Jeff DeFinney 
with just under 8 1/2 minutes remaining in the second quarter, cutting St. 
Paul's lead to 10-7. 
</P>
<P>
 MAJOR UPSET 
</P>
<P>
 Hoover High surprises Crescenta Valley, 34-20, in a Pacific League game. C14 
</P>
</TEXT>
