<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; DEL REY LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola 37, Alemany 0 -- Junior running back Mike Vanis ran for three 
touchdowns to lead the Cubs (6-1, 1-1) at Alemany. 
</P>
<P>
 Vanis had 13 carries for 126 yards scored from one and two yards in the first 
quarter as Loyola scored on its first three possessions to take a 16-0 lead. 
Vanis scored from 40 yards early in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cubs forced three interceptions and held Alemany (1-4-2, 0-2) to 114 total 
yards. LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
