<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; MISSION LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN BOLT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Francis 21, Serra 12 -- Running back Darin Maxwell rushed for 93 yards and 
a touchdown and quarterback Brian Rucker passed for two touchdowns for St. 
Francis (4-2-1, 1-1) at Serra. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Francis forced four turnovers, two of which led to touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Maxwell opened the scoring with a one-yard run in the second quarter and the 
Golden Knights took a 14-0 halftime lead on a one-yard touchdown pass from 
Rucker to wide receiver Chris Ross. Ross caught four passes for 36 yards and 
Rucker completed seven of 12 for 103 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Francis took a 21-0 lead early in the third quarter but Serra (4-3, 0-2) 
came back on touchdowns passes of eight and 13 yards by quarterback DeWayne 
Hervey, who was eight of 20 for 140 yards. KEVIN BOLT 
</P>
</TEXT>
