<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon 25, Burroughs 16 -- Shaun Kelso ran for three fourth-quarter touchdowns 
and finished with 134 yards in 13 carries to lift the host Cowboys to a 
come-from-behind victory over Burroughs (2-5, 0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon (2-4-1, 1-1) trailed, 10-0, late in the third quarter before exploding 
for all its points in a 12 minutes of the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon quarterback Ahjeron Palmer cut the deficit to 10-6 with a 12-yard 
touchdown run with 2:34 left in the third quarter. Kelso then scored on runs of 
12 and five yards. RON STAPP 
