By JASON SANDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nordhoff 41, Calabasas 0 -- Running back Josh Hawkins rushed 22 times for 269 
yards and four touchdowns to lead the Rangers (4-3, 1-0) at Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawkins, who has 1,032 yards this season, began the scoring early in the 
second quarter on a one-yard run. He later scored on runs of 15, 54 and 90 
yards as Nordhoff rolled up 420 yards of offense. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas running back Ken Morris rushed for 86 yards against a stingy Ranger 
defense, led by linebacker Shane Barrett, who had a seven-yard interception 
return for a touchdown in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas (2-5, 1-1) gained 193 yards of offense. JASON SANDS 
