<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUARTZ HILL DEFEATS HIGHLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY PRICE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior quarterback Damein Kendrid ran for a touchdown and passed for another 
during a 2-minute 29-second stretch of the third quarter to lead Quartz Hill 
High to a 13-7 Golden League victory over Highland on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 With Quartz Hill (4-1-2, 1-0-1 in league play) trailing, 7-0, midway through 
the quarter, Kendrid capped a four-play, 38-yard drive by running 13 yards for 
a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 The drive was set up when linebacker Eric Gray recovered a fumble by Highland 
quarterback Jason Carr. 
</P>
<P>
 On Quartz Hill's next series, a two-play drive, Kendrid threw deep to Andy 
Rethi, who outreached defensive back Marcus Prevost for the ball and scored. 
</P>
<P>
 Highland (4-3, 1-1) missed a chance when safety Monte Reed intercepted a pass 
by Kendrid at the four-yard line. But Reed fumbled the ball, which was scooped 
up by Highland's Norris Theus. 
</P>
<P>
 Tailback LeDarral Hollingsworth gained three yards to the one on the first 
play, but Carr was sacked for a four-yard loss, Highland was called for holding 
and Carr threw an incomplete pass before John Hall missed a 33-yard field-goal 
attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Highland took a 7-0 lead when Theus returned a punt 60 yards for a touchdown 
in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Highland's Kirk Brown missed a 40-yard field-goal attempt in the third 
quarter. GERRY PRICE 
</P>
</TEXT>
