<HEADLINE>
<P>
AGOURA TRIPS SIMI VALLEY, 22-20 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA GRALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Agoura High built a 22-point halftime lead and held on to upset previously 
undefeated Simi Valley, 22-20, in a Marmonte League game Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley (5-1-1, 3-1), which benefited from three Agoura turnovers in the 
second half, began its comeback in the third quarter when Robert Gonzalez 
intercepted an Eric Fitzgerald pass and returned it 19 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pioneers closed to within 22-13 when J.J. Washington caught a 28-yard 
touchdown pass from Tim Bennett early in the fourth quarter, but Bennett's pass 
fell incomplete on the two-point conversion try. 
</P>
<P>
 Washington (six receptions, 129 yards) caught a 16-yard touchdown pass from 
Bennett with 5 minutes 49 seconds left. Tim Wolleck kicked the extra point to 
draw Simi Valley within 22-20. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley had one last chance to take the lead late in the fourth quarter, 
but Craig Ohm intercepted a Bennett pass and the Chargers (3-4, 3-1) ran out 
the clock. Bennett, who threw four interceptions, completed nine of 25 for 153 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Fitzgerald, who completed 10 of 21 for 134 yards, tossed three scoring passes 
in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Capretta (four catches, 70 yards) caught a 45-yard scoring pass from 
Fitzgerald in the first quarter and added a five-yard touchdown pass from 
Fitzgerald in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Tommy Kim rushed for 82 yards in 19 carries and caught a 20-yard scoring pass 
from Fitzgerald in the second period. LISA GRALL 
</P>
</TEXT>
