<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAVIS (237 YARDS) PACES VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES CHESNUTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aaron Davis rushed for 237 yards and four touchdowns in 11 carries to lead 
Ventura High to a 48-25 victory over Rio Mesa in a Channel League game Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis' second score, a 27-yard run late in the first quarter, reclaimed the 
lead for the Cougars, (2-5, 2-2) who didn't trail again. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis then broke an 85-yard run up the middle to give the Cougars a 22-7 lead 
and Ventura was on its way. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spartans (1-6, 0-4) were led by quarterback Farhaad Azimi, who completed 
10 of 20 passes for 140 yards with one interception. Azimi also rushed for 29 
yards, including a five-yard touchdown run, and added a 28-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura quarterback Erik Olson was five of seven for 94 yards and rushed for 
58 yards in seven carries, including a two-yard touchdown run. JAMES CHESNUTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
