<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; HOOVER SWAMPS CRESCENTA VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoover High beat Crescenta Valley at its own game Friday night, using tough 
defense and ball control to upset the Falcons, 34-20, in a Pacific League game 
at Glendale High. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior running back Hung Huynh scored three second-quarter touchdowns to give 
Hoover (3-4, 1-1 in league play) a 28-7 halftime lead.Huynh rushed for 103 
yards in 21 carries in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "We wanted this game really bad," Hoover Coach Dennis Hughes said. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley (5-2, 0-2) opened the scoring with two minutes left in the 
first quarter with a 64-yard pass play from John Watts to Jose Escalera, but 
Hoover answered before the end of the quarter with a 69-yard scoring play on a 
pass from Carlos Valadez to Eric Jenkins. 
</P>
<P>
 Marko Msrobian kicked a 48-yard field goal for Hoover in the third quarter and 
added a 31-yard kick in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Watts was 10 of 15 for 211 yards and two touchdowns, both to Escalera. DARIN 
ESPER 
</P>
</TEXT>
