<P>
ROUNDUP; NORTHRIDGE SWEEPS IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Heather Anderson had 14 kills and 19 digs to lead Cal State Northridge to a 
15-9, 15-9, 15-8 victory over host Santa Clara in a nonconference women's 
volleyball match Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Aimee Stone and Missy Clements each added 12 kills as Northridge (12-7) won 
its second match in a row and its fifth in the last six. 
</P>
<P>
 Ana Kristich had 10 kills and added a match-high five blocks for the Matadors, 
who are five games above .500 for the first time this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Kathleen Shannon contributed 44 assists for Northridge, which does not play 
again until a Nov. 1 match at Loyola Marymount. 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Tozi had 12 kills and 14 digs for Santa Clara (6-15). 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran d. Redlands 15-5, 15-3, 15-6 -- Freshman Jamey Light tied a Cal 
Lutheran record with nine service aces and Megan Falde led a balanced Lady 
Regals attack with nine kills as Cal Lutheran easily defeated Redlands in a 
Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference match at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
 Light tied a record established by Brenda Frafjord in a five-game match 
against Christian Heritage in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran, the second-ranked team in the NCAA Division III West Region, 
improved to 16-7 overall, 8-0 in conference play. WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
