 Moorpark 3, Oxnard, 0 -- Maureen O'Hare scored one goal and assisted on 
another to lead Moorpark (7-3, 5-1) in a Western State Conference match at 
home. Heather Heit and Lori Haskel also scored for Moorpark and Mariah Ventre 
added an assist. 
</P>
<P>
 Goalkeeper Amy Fisher made three saves. HIGH SCHOOL WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
 Crespi 11, Notre Dame 6 -- David Brea and Mike Scarcelli each scored four 
goals as Crespi won a Mission league match at Pierce College. Notre Dame tied 
Crespi at 4-4 but the Celts (13-9, 4-2) countered with six consecutive goals. 
Chris Crowley led Notre Dame (15-6, 3-3) with three goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 12, Westlake 11 (OT) -- Steve Lazar scored the game-winning goal 
in the second period of overtime in a Marmonte League match at Newbury Park. 
David Block had five goals, four assists and nine steals for Westlake (0-5 in 
league play). HIGH SCHOOL VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Buckley d. Holy Martyrs 3-15, 15-12, 15-10, 9-15, 16-14 -- Nicole Fitzpatrick 
had 15 kills and Stephanie Juhos added six service aces as Buckley (3-12, 2-6) 
won a Liberty League match at home. 
</P>
