<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; 'L.A. STORIES' SADDLES UP WITH CITY POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 KCBS-TV Channel 2's "L.A. Stories" will take to the streets Sunday at 10:30 
a.m. for a visit to the Los Angeles Police Department's elite mounted division. 
Members of this special unit -- composed of 31 officers, nine civilians and 34 
horses -- are subjected to rigorous training for street patrol and crowd 
control. 
</P>
<P>
 The show will also feature a look at Colors United, a performance program for 
urban youths that teaches expressions of creative arts as an alternative to 
gangs, drugs and violence. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</TEXT>
