PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; FOOTMAN CARRIES THE LOAD FOR ESPERANZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Esperanza senior tailback Dahrin Footman carried the Aztecs to a 21-7 Sunset 
League victory over Huntington Beach Friday night at Valencia High. 
</P>
<P>
 Footman carried 29 times for 277 yards, scoring all three Aztec touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza remained unbeaten in league play heading into next Thursday's 
showdown with undefeated league-rival Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 Footman scored his first touchdown on a two-yard run 51 seconds into the 
second quarter. On the next series, he leaped over the Oiler defense for a 
one-yard score with 3 minutes 37 seconds remaining in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach senior quarterback Jason Bartusick cut the Aztec lead with 22 
seconds left in the half, as he scrambled through the Esperanza defense for a 
nine-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
 Footman gave the Aztecs insurance midway through the third quarter, when he 
rushed for 52 yards and his third touchdown.  
</P>
<P>
 The Esperanza defense held Huntington Beach to 133 yards total offense, only 
nine yards on the ground. 
</P>
<P>
 Bartusick was sacked six times, the last a combined effort by Jeremy Viscusi 
and Sean Garney with 2:41 remaining in the game. The Aztecs took over and 
didn't relinquish the ball again. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza totaled 418 yards in offense. Quarterback Chris Stretch completed 
nine of 14 passes for 155 yards. Junior tight end Brian Forth had six catches 
for 141 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Bartusick completed 15 of 27 passes for 124 yards. David VanHoorebeke had five 
catches for 66 yards. DALE RUHE 
</P>
</TEXT>
