<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; FOUNTAIN VALLEY SLAMS EIGHTH-RANKED 
MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley scored on four of its first five possessions and cruised to a 
31-8 Sunset League victory over eighth-ranked Marina Friday at Huntington Beach 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Barons (4-3, 2-0 in league) thoroughly dominated the first half, taking 
advantage of two Marina interceptions that led to the first two touchdowns.The 
Barons outgained Marina, 222-49, in the first half and took a 24-0 lead. Marina 
is 5-2 and 0-2. 
</P>
<P>
 After Yamile Fernandez intercepted Matt Roberson's first pass, Fountain Valley 
drove 52 yards on 11 plays, scoring on a 10-yard pass from quarterback Chris 
Ponchak to Michael Rumford with 3 minutes 6 seconds left in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 On Marina's next possession, Devin O'Day intercepted another Roberson pass, 
giving the Barons the ball at their own 49. 
</P>
<P>
 After a seven-play drive, Matt Harrison scored from one yard with 10:24 left 
in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Ponchak completed 10 of 23 passes for 152 yards and two touchdowns. He also 
rushed for another score. 
</P>
<P>
 On the opening possession of the second half, Marina drove 80 yards in 12 
plays and scored on a 33-yard pass play from Roberson to Aron Bergman. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 24-8, Marina drove to the Fountain Valley 12-yard line before 
turning it over on downs. The Vikings never came close to the end zone again. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley finished the scoring with a 35-yard touchdown pass from 
Ponchak to Joey Rozek with 3:56 left in the game. KEN HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
