<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; CENTURY LEAGUE; SECOND-QUARTER EFFORT 
KEYS VILLA PARK ROUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sean McMahon threw for 116 yards and two touchdowns to lead Villa Park to a 
42-8 victory over El Modena in a Century League game Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Playing in front of a homecoming crowd of 2,500 at El Modena, the Spartans 
(6-1, 1-1) blew out the Vanguards (2-5, 0-2) with a 28-point second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park scored 35 points in a seven-minute span between the end of the 
first quarter and the middle of the second. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spartans took a 7-0 lead on a 23-yard run by sophomore Franklin Haynes 
with 1 minute 5 seconds left in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park recovered an El Modena fumble on the ensuing kickoff at the 
Vanguard 18-yard line. After a 17-yard pass from McMahon to Kris Fisher, 
McMahon scored from one yard out for a 14-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spartans stopped El Modena on its next possession and got the ball back at 
the Vanguard 19 when Tony D'Amato recovered a bad snap on a punt. 
</P>
<P>
 Two plays later, D'Amato gave the Spartans a 21-0 lead when he scored on a 
five-yard run with 9:16 left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Less than two minutes later, Villa Park made it 28-0 on a nine-yard pass from 
McMahon to Fisher. 
</P>
<P>
 Taylor Elliott recovered an El Modena fumble on the ensuing kickoff at the 
Vanguard five, and Dave Martinez went in on the next play for a 35-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spartans made it 42-0 with 4:22 left in the third quarter when McMahon hit 
Matt Welch for an 18-yard score. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena finally got on the board early in the fourth quarter when Jason Said 
scored on a one-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park's running game was dominant. At one point late in the game, the 
Spartans were averaging more than 10 yards per carry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
