<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Western High's David Bell scored 20 points to pace Western to a 38-20 victory 
over Magnolia in Orange League play Friday night at Glover Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 With Western trailing, 7-0, in the first quarter, Bell returned a kickoff 86 
yards to tie the score.Later in the quarter, he broke through and blocked Tony 
Iliescu's punt and returned it 23 yards for a score to give Western (6-0-1, 
1-0-1) a 21-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell kicked a 32-yard field goal with 10:35 left in the second quarter to give 
Western a 24-7 lead. He added five conversion kicks. 
</P>
<P>
 Justin Starkey gave Western its first lead when he caught a 23-yard touchdown 
pass from Dean Chambers with 3:03 left in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia's Ryan Heiman recovered a fumble by Chambers fumble and seven plays 
later, Robert Nicols passed 11 yards to Carlos Martin for the game's first 
score. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicols was the only highlight for Magnolia (1-6, 0-2). The senior quarterback 
threw a 34-yard touchdown pass to Eric Webber and returned a Western fumble 85 
yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicols, however, was intercepted by Western's Chris Ostergaard, who returned 
it 43 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Frembling scored the other touchdown for Western on a three-yard run in 
the third quarter. Frembling led Western in rushing with 41 yards in eight 
carries. RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
