<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; SANTIAGO'S PALACIOS 
HELPS SPOIL HOMECOMING FOR LA QUINTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANDY EISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jose Palacios rushed for 121 yards and scored two touchdowns as Santiago 
spoiled La Quinta's homecoming by winning Friday night's Garden Grove League 
game, 26-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Palacios ran the final 20 yards of the opening drive for the Cavaliers (3-4, 
2-1), and added a one-yard plunge midway through the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cavaliers added two quick touchdowns midway through the third quarter to 
put the game away. Following an Octavio Villa interception, Anthony Callari 
capped a three-play, 32-yard drive with an 18-yard scoring run with 5 minutes 
52 seconds left in the period. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Eckert then recovered a fumble on the Aztec five on the next play from 
scrimmage, and Tom Sokanthong carried it in from there on the following play 
with 4:59 remaining in the period. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aztecs (1-6, 0-4) avoided the shutout on the first play of the fourth 
quarter when Sokanthong dropped back to punt, and chased a wild snap out of the 
end zone for a safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Cavaliers quarterback Christian Cortez completed two of 10 passes for 38 
yards, but rushed for 36 yards had a key interception early in the game. 
Callari finished with 50 yards in six carries. ANDY EISER 
</P>
