<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; LAST-MINUTE TOUCHDOWN LIFTS SUNNY HILLS 
OVER FULLERTON, 13-12 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Greg Garand hit Jeff Renaud with a 12-yard touchdown pass with 43 seconds left 
to give Sunny Hills a 13-12 Freeway League victory over Fullerton Friday night 
at Buena Park High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers had driven from their 15-yard line to the Indian five in the final 
two minutes, but Garand was sacked twice for a loss of seven yards.On 
fourth-and-goal from the 12, Garand then found Renaud open in the right side of 
the end zone for the go-ahead score. A two-point conversion attempt failed. 
</P>
<P>
 The game-winner was the second touchdown pass to Renaud from Garand, who 
completed 17 of 34 passes for 219 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton had scored first after a short punt from the end zone by Sunny Hills 
(2-5, 1-1) gave the Indians the ball on the Lancer 27-yard line. Running back 
John Wilkie's one-yard touchdown run gave Fullerton a 6-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers took a 7-6 lead when Renaud caught a 30-yard pass from Garand on 
fourth down with 6 minutes 32 seconds left the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (4-3, 1-1) had three scoring chances in the third quarter. After a 
fumble by Chris Velotta, the Indians' Ryan Gregory missed a 37-yard field-goal 
attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 A two-yard punt by the Lancers gave Fullerton similar field position, but 
again Gregory missed a field-goal attempt, this time from 35 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton took a 12-7 lead after another Velotta fumble set up a short drive 
that was capped by a one-yard touchdown run by Christopher Young with 3:28 left 
in the third quarter. JASON HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
