</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michelle Schneider of Los Alamitos has orally committed to attend Stanford 
next year on a softball scholarship, her coach, Jami Shannon, said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Schneider, a shortstop with a .955 fielding average, was a Times All-County 
and Southern Section Division I player who batted .415 with 24 runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Laura Echolds, a middle blocker at Esperanza, orally committed to play 
volleyball at Santa Clara, Esperanza Coach Kurt Kersten said. 
</P>
<P>
 Last season, the 6-foot Echolds was selected first-team All-Empire League. She 
is a three-year starter. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Owens of Calvary Chapel, a Times all-county selection last season, 
orally committed to play volleyball at Colorado.  
</P>
<P>
 Owens, a 5-foot-10 outside hitter, was an All-Southern Section Division V 
selection last season and a second-team all-county pick by The Times. 
</P>
