 Brian Brown scored seven goals to lead third-ranked Foothill to a 13-8 victory 
over ninth-ranked Newport Harbor in a nonleague water polo game Friday at 
Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 Five of Brown's goals came in the first half, which ended with the score tied, 
5-5. The Knights (14-3) scored five goals in the third quarter to take control. 
</P>
<P>
 Gabe Wyatt had three goals and Andy Betz had two for Newport Harbor (9-9). 
Robbie Arroyo scored twice for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Brown had seven saves for Foothill, and Graham Harvey eight for the 
Sailors. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
