<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST TOPS SOUTHWESTERN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West discovered a new tailback tandem Friday night as the Rustlers 
hammered Southwestern, 49-10, at Orange Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
 Freshmen John Sims and Damien Cook combined for 160 rushing yards and five 
touchdowns and the Rustlers improved to 2-1 in the Central Division of the 
Mission Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rustlers started the season with a host of strong tailbacks, but the 
numbers have dwindled. Thomas Green left the team, two others decided to be 
redshirted, and Mark Crowley suffered a season-ending broken leg last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Sims, who had rushed for just 60 yards this season, ran for a career-high 96 
yards in 10 carries and scored on runs of two and six yards to help the 
Rustlers build a 35-3 lead by halftime. Cook contributed 64 yards in 12 carries 
and caught four passes for 114 yards, scoring on receptions of 62 and 31 yards 
and adding an 18-yard scoring run. 
</P>
<P>
 After losing a fumble on its first possession, Golden West scored on its next 
four possessions to lead, 28-0. Freshman quarterback Brian Schneider threw for 
219 yards in the opening half and a career-best 266 yards in the game, 
completing 10 of 13 passes. He connected for three scores, two to Cook in 
addition to a 71-yard touchdown pass to Don Ruberio that opened the scoring 
seven minutes into the game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
