<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; AH SIGH WINS IN ED BURKE TRIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Frank Nakamura's Ah Sigh returned from a two-month layoff to win the first of 
six trials to the $180,000 Ed Burke Memorial Futurity by two lengths. 
</P>
<P>
 Under John Creager, Ah Sigh paid $3.00 to win. Runninbac returned $4.00 and 
$3.60 and Alibis Assets paid $3.40. 
</P>
<P>
 The extremely fast winning time of 17.57 seconds for the 350 yards guarantees 
the Charlie Bloomquist-trainee a spot in the Nov. 4 final. 
</P>
<P>
 By comparison, Chenilles Dasher won her trial in 17.73 in the next race on the 
card Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the fifth for Ah Sigh, who previously won the Miss 
Kindergarten Futurity and finished third in the Governor's Cup Futurity, her 
only career defeat. STACY PIGOTT 
