<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: IRVINE; 18-YEAR-OLD SUSPECT ARRESTED IN JANUARY TURTLE 
ROCK SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police arrested an 18-year-old man Friday in connection with the Jan. 20 
murder of a Turtle Rock woman in her home. 
</P>
<P>
 Earl Rhoney, a former Irvine resident, was arrested just before 2 p.m. on 
suspicion of homicide and burglary, according to Lt. Sam Allevato.He was booked 
into the Orange County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of 45-year-old Patricia Lea Pratt was found in her bedroom at the end 
of a cul-de-sac on Windflower by her husband, Paul Pratt, when he returned just 
before midnight from a business meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 At the time of the killing, police said Patricia Pratt, a service manager for 
PacTel Cellular, may have been bludgeoned to death when she interrupted a 
burglary. Several items of value had been taken from the house, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rhoney was arrested after his release from Orange County Juvenile Hall, where 
he was being held on a burglary charge, Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police would not say what linked Rhoney to the crime that rocked the 
community.  
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said Pratt had been killed, probably with blows to the upper 
torso, sometime between 5:30 and 11:45 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Police officers distributed more than 400 flyers in the neighborhood following 
the killing in hopes that witnesses would provide them with some leads.  
</P>
<P>
 Pratt's death was the fourth homicide in Irvine since 1990. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
