<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ANGELES TIMES SPECIAL REPORT / BASEBALL; WORLD SERIES MEMORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1905-Christy Mathewson threw three shutouts, including one on one day's rest, 
as John McGraw's New York Giants defeated the Philadelphia Athletics in five 
games, all shutouts. 
</P>
<P>
 1911-Frank Baker hit two home runs in the Series, earning the nickname Home 
Run Baker, as Connie Mack's Philadelphia Athletics defeated the New York Giants 
in six games. 
</P>
<P>
 1919-In the Black Sox scandal, eight Chicago White Sox agreed to intentionally 
lose the Series to the Cincinnati Reds for $100,000. The Reds won, five games 
to three. 
</P>
<P>
 1924-Walter Johnson won Game 7 in relief after losing two starts as the 
Washington Senators won their first World Series. 
</P>
<P>
 1932-Babe Ruth's final Series featured his "Called Shot" in Game 3 in which he 
did or didn't point to center field before hitting a home run there. The 
Yankees swept the Cubs. 
</P>
<P>
 1941-A passed ball in Game 4 by the Brooklyn Dodgers' Mickey Owen on strike 
three with two outs in the ninth led to four runs and a five-game Series 
victory for the Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
 1946-The St. Louis Cardinals' Enos Slaughter scored from first on a single in 
the eighth inning to win game 7 against the Boston Red Sox, 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
 1954-Willie Mays' over-the-shoulder basket catch of Vic Wertz's drive in Game 
1 propelled the New York Giants to a sweep of the Cleveland Indians. 
</P>
<P>
 1956-Don Larsen threw a perfect game on Oct. 8, striking out seven in Game 5 
for the Yankees, who defeated the Brooklyn Dodgers in seven games. 
</P>
<P>
 1960-The Pittsburgh Pirates defeated the New York Yankees on Bill Mazeroski's 
leadoff home run in the bottom of ninth inning of Game 7. 
</P>
<P>
 1969-The once hapless 1962 expansion New York Mets stunned the Baltimore 
Orioles in five games, earning the nickname "Miracle Mets." 
</P>
<P>
 1971-Roberto Clemente reached his career pinnacle, leading the Pittsburgh 
Pirates past the Orioles in seven games. Clemente, who batted .414, died after 
1972 season. 
</P>
<P>
 1975-The Reds' seven-game victory was overshadowed by the image of Carlton 
Fisk frantically waving his arms as his 12th-inning home run won Game 6. 
</P>
<P>
 1977-Reggie Jackson hit three home runs against the Dodgers in Game 6 to 
clinch the Series for the Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
 1978-Bob Welch struck out Reggie Jackson, who fouled off three full-count 
pitches, in the ninth with two runners on base to win Game 2; the Yankees won 
the Series in six games. 
</P>
<P>
 1986-Mookie Wilson's ground ball went through the legs of Boston first baseman 
Bill Buckner, allowing the game-winning run in Game 6. The Mets then won Game 
7. 
</P>
<P>
 1988-An injured Kirk Gibson hit a two-run homer in the ninth off Dennis 
Eckersley to win Game 1 and the Dodgers went on to defeat the A's in five. 
</P>
<P>
 1989-The Earthquake Series was won by the Oakland A's in four games, but only 
after Game 3 was postponed for 10 days after an earthquake hit the Bay Area. 
</P>
<P>
 1993-Joe Carter's three-run home run with one out in the ninth inning of Game 
6 clinched the Series for the Toronto Blue Jays. 
</P>
<P>
 1994-The World Series is canceled because of a labor dispute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
